    dc:creator "Sawicki, Thomas R.", "Sisco, Joshua M." ;
    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "Molecular and morphological analyses reveal a new hypogean species of amphipod in the genus Crangonyx Bate, 1859 (Crustacea: Crangonyctidae) within the floridanus species complex, from Suwannee County, Florida" ;
    bibo:endPage "1286" ;
    bibo:issue "21 - 24" ;
    bibo:journal "Journal of Natural History" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2023-09-14" ;
    bibo:startPage "1257" ;
    bibo:volume "57" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10015552>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10015554>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10015556>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10015558>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10015560>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10015562>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10015564>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10015566> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10015552>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Crangonyx stinei sp. n. holotype female, Wes Skiles Peacock Springs State Park, Suwannee County, Florida (UFIZ 70388), 5.57 mm (a); allotype male, Wes Skiles Peacock Springs State Park, Suwannee County, Florida (UFIZ 70383), 5.27 mm (b). Holotype image taken within 24 hours of collection and before alcohol preservation; allotype image taken after extended period in 100% ethanol. Scale bar = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10015552/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10015554>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Crangonyx stinei sp. n. holotype female, Wes Skiles Peacock Springs State Park, Suwannee County, Florida (UFIZ 70388), 5.57 mm: antenna 1 (accessory flagellum and aesthetasc enlarged) (a); antenna 2 (b); Crangonyx stinei sp. n. paratype female Wes Skiles Peacock Springs State Park, Suwannee County, Florida (UFIZ 70387), 3.81 mm: left mandible (incisor and lacinia mobilis enlarged) (c); Crangonyx stinei sp. n. holotype female: right mandible (palp omitted, lacinia mobilis enlarged) (d). Scale bars = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10015554/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10015556>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Crangonyx stinei sp. n. paratype female, Wes Skiles Peacock Springs State Park, Suwannee County, Florida (UFIZ 70387), 3.81 mm: upper lip (a); holotype female, Wes Skiles Peacock Springs State Park, Suwannee County, Florida (UFIZ 70388), 5.57 mm: lower lip (b); maxilla 1 (outer plate spineteeth enlarged) (c); maxilla 2 (d); maxilliped (inner plate apical margin enlarged) (e). Scale bars = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10015556/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10015558>
    dc:description "Figure 5. Crangonyx stinei sp. n. holotype female, Wes Skiles Peacock Springs State Park, Suwannee County, Florida (UFIZ 70388), 5.57 mm: gnathopod 1 (palmar margin and dactyl enlarged) (a); gnathopod 2 (palmar margin and dactyl enlarged) (b); gnathopod 2 brood plate (c). Scale bar = 1 mm (scale bar does not reference enlarged palmar margin and dactyl)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10015558/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10015560>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Crangonyx stinei sp. n. holotype female, Wes Skiles Peacock Springs State Park, Suwannee County, Florida (UFIZ 70388), 5.57 mm: pereopod 3 (a); pereopod 4 (b); pereopod 5 (c); pereopod 6 (d); pereopod 7 (e). Scale bar = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10015560/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10015562>
    dc:description "Figure 7. Crangonyx stinei sp. n. holotype female, Wes Skiles Peacock Springs State Park, Suwannee County, Florida (UFIZ 70388), 5.57 mm: pleopod 1 (coupling hooks enlarged) (a); pleopod 2 coupling hooks (b); pleopod 3 coupling hooks (c); epimera 1–3 (d); uropod 1 (e); uropod 2 (f); uropod 3 (g); telson (h). Scale bars = 1 mm (a–f); 0.5 mm (g); 0.25 mm (h)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10015562/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10015564>
    dc:description "Figure 8. Crangonyx stinei sp. n. allotype male, Wes Skiles Peacock Springs State Park, Suwannee County, Florida (UFIZ 70383), 5.27 mm: antenna 2 (calceoli enlarged) (a); Crangonyx stinei sp. n. paratype male, Wes Skiles Peacock Springs State Park, Suwannee County, Florida (UFIZ 70392), 3.5 mm: uropod 1 (b); uropod 2 (outer ramus enlarged) (d); uropod 3 (d); telson (e). Scale bars = 1 mm (a); 0.5 mm (b–d); 0.25 mm (e)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10015564/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10015566>
    dc:description "Figure 9. Crangonyx stinei sp. n. allotype male, Wes Skiles Peacock Springs State Park, Suwannee County, Florida (UFIZ 70383), 5.27 mm: gnathopod 1 (palmar margin and dactyl enlarged) (a); gnathopod 2 (palmar margin and dactyl enlarged) (b); pereopod 5 (c); pereopod 6 basis posterior margin (d); pereopod 7 basis posterior margin (e). Scale bars = 1 mm (scale bar does not reference enlarged palmar margin and dactyl)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10015566/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

